The paper introduces a fundamental result relevant for Answer Set programming and planning, which are subfields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with the existence of stable models of logic programs, which is a topic in logic and computation (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also introduces a new canonical form for logic programs, which could be relevant for data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
